#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.25:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Puggalavagga"
msgstr "3. Persons"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Vajirūpamasutta"
msgstr "25. Like Diamond"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.124"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.25:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“These three people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an3.25:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.25:1.3"
msgid ""
"Arukūpamacitto puggalo, vijjūpamacitto puggalo, vajirūpamacitto puggalo."
msgstr ""
"A person with a mind like an open sore, a person with a mind like lightning, "
"and a person with a mind like diamond."

msgctxt "an3.25:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, arukūpamacitto puggalo?"
msgstr "And who has a mind like an open sore?"

msgctxt "an3.25:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kodhano hoti upāyāsabahulo "
msgstr "It’s someone who is irritable and bad-tempered. "

msgctxt "an3.25:1.6"
msgid ""
"appampi vutto samāno abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca "
"dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti."
msgstr ""
"Even when lightly criticized they lose their temper, becoming annoyed, "
"hostile, and hard-hearted, and they display annoyance, hate, and bitterness."

#. VAR: duṭṭhāruko → duṭṭhārukā (bj)
#. VAR: kaṭhalāya → kaṭhalena (bj) | kathalāya (mr) | kaṭhalena-kathalena (aṭṭha.)
#. VAR: ghaṭṭito → ghaṭṭitā (bj)
#. VAR: āsavaṃ deti → assandati (bj) | assavanoti (si)
msgctxt "an3.25:1.7"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, duṭṭhāruko kaṭṭhena vā kaṭhalāya vā ghaṭṭito bhiyyoso "
"mattāya āsavaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""
"They’re like a festering sore, which, when you hit it with a stick or a "
"stone, discharges even more."

msgctxt "an3.25:1.8"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo kodhano hoti upāyāsabahulo "
msgstr "In the same way, someone is irritable and bad-tempered. "

msgctxt "an3.25:1.9"
msgid ""
"appampi vutto samāno abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca "
"dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti."
msgstr ""
"Even when lightly criticized they lose their temper, becoming annoyed, "
"hostile, and hard-hearted, and they display annoyance, hate, and bitterness."

msgctxt "an3.25:1.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, arukūpamacitto puggalo."
msgstr "This is called a person with a mind like an open sore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.25:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, vijjūpamacitto puggalo?"
msgstr "And who has a mind like lightning?"

msgctxt "an3.25:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "an3.25:2.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ vijjantarikāya "
"rūpāni passeyya;"
msgstr ""
"They’re like a person with keen eyes in the dark of the night, who sees by a "
"flash of lightning."

msgctxt "an3.25:2.4"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, someone truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is "
"the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is "
"the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "an3.25:2.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vijjūpamacitto puggalo."
msgstr "This is called a person with a mind like lightning."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.25:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, vajirūpamacitto puggalo?"
msgstr "And who has a mind like diamond?"

msgctxt "an3.25:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ "
"paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an3.25:3.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vajirassa natthi kiñci abhejjaṃ maṇi vā pāsāṇo vā;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a diamond, which can’t be cut by anything at all, not even a gem "
"or a stone."

msgctxt "an3.25:3.4"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, someone realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom "
"by wisdom in this very life. …"

msgctxt "an3.25:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vajirūpamacitto puggalo."
msgstr "This is called a person with a mind like diamond."

msgctxt "an3.25:3.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti."
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.25:3.7"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
